msg: WICKET-3333 Links with multiple parameters are wrongly generated
WICKET-2829 Tag attributes values are not escaped properly during writeOutput
By default do not escape the value of TextField. The value is already escaped by WICKET-2829.
If the user wants to see the non-escaped value in the text field then she needs to explicitly call .setEscapeModelStrings(true).

author: marvin
msg: Always call XSRETURN at the end of a bound method/function.  Remove PUTBACK
calls which are now *always* unreachable rather than sometimes unreachable.
Note that all PUTBACK does is update the global var holding the Perl stack
pointer from the local copy; XSRETURN also sets this global var.
